\index{coreRegistersDef::stack\_pointer (C++ member)@\spxentry{coreRegistersDef::stack\_pointer}\spxextra{C++ member}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv4N16coreRegistersDef13stack_pointerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv3N16coreRegistersDef13stack_pointerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv2N16coreRegistersDef13stack_pointerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:coreRegistersDef::stack_pointer__uint32_tP}}
\pysigstartsignatures
\pysigstartmultiline
\pysigline{\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:structcoreRegistersDef_1adeea21c076fcb4f87d1ecaed25895b6d}}\DUrole{n}{uint32\_t}\DUrole{w}{  }\DUrole{p}{*}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{\DUrole{n}{stack\_pointer}}}}
\pysigstopmultiline
\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
The Stack Pointer (SP) is register R13. 

\sphinxAtStartPar
In Thread mode, bit{[}1{]} of the CONTROL register indicates the stack pointer to use:\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
0: Main Stack Pointer (MSP). This is the reset value.

\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
1: Process Stack Pointer (PSP). On reset, the processor loads the MSP with the value from address 0x00000000. 

\end{itemize}


\end{fulllineitems}

\index{coreRegistersDef::link\_register (C++ member)@\spxentry{coreRegistersDef::link\_register}\spxextra{C++ member}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv4N16coreRegistersDef13link_registerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv3N16coreRegistersDef13link_registerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv2N16coreRegistersDef13link_registerE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:coreRegistersDef::link_register__uint32_t}}
\pysigstartsignatures
\pysigstartmultiline
\pysigline{\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:structcoreRegistersDef_1ae52ca5652b22e7db3d77ae73f1062fa2}}\DUrole{n}{uint32\_t}\DUrole{w}{  }\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{\DUrole{n}{link\_register}}}}
\pysigstopmultiline
\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
The Link Register (LR) is register R14. 

\sphinxAtStartPar
It stores the return information for subroutines, function calls, and exceptions. On reset, the processor loads the LR value 0xFFFFFFFF. 

\end{fulllineitems}

\index{coreRegistersDef::program\_counter (C++ member)@\spxentry{coreRegistersDef::program\_counter}\spxextra{C++ member}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv4N16coreRegistersDef15program_counterE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv3N16coreRegistersDef15program_counterE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:_CPPv2N16coreRegistersDef15program_counterE}}\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:coreRegistersDef::program_counter__uint32_tP}}
\pysigstartsignatures
\pysigstartmultiline
\pysigline{\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{source_code:structcoreRegistersDef_1a8b5a9b4ec34711856612808b662fe434}}\DUrole{n}{uint32\_t}\DUrole{w}{  }\DUrole{p}{*}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{\DUrole{n}{program\_counter}}}}
\pysigstopmultiline
\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
The Program Counter (PC) is register R15. 

\sphinxAtStartPar
It contains the current program address. On reset, the processor loads the PC with the value of the reset vector, which is at address 0x00000004. Bit{[}0{]} of the value is loaded into the EPSR T\sphinxhyphen{}bit at reset and must be 1. 

\end{fulllineitems}

\end{itemize}
